column5: Looks like your all ready.  Nice looking rig for sure!
Nice looking ride! Looks like she has all the bells and whistles.
Beautiful.  A big wide tiller is the way to go.  Nothing but space.
never met a Lund I didn't like

She looks different with no riggers on it! Is that the same boat you've had for a while now, or a new one?  Haven't seen you around darlington or newcastle salmon fishing for a while....that I've noticed anyways.  S.
I like it,I like it alot.Very nice.
Nice ride !  Git er Slimed !!!Congrats to ya.  Paul
I have it's twin, and they are great boats, handle rougher water quite well!!
Long time, no see...   Walleye eh? You know if its food you want you can buy 'em at the grocery store!
Gotta love a lund. Whats the hp on that merc??
Yeah...sweet rig.  I have a walk-though 16 as my new boat and really wish I had gotten a tiller, like my old deep 14 footer.
